items.abstract:
<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>
<jats:p>This paper discusses two different approaches to microanalysis of the soil medium. It presents testing results collected by electromicroscopy, which requires special sample preparation, and a non-destructive method, requiring no sample preparation and using a computer-assisted tomograph. The paper presents:</jats:p>
<jats:p>• Applicability of microstructure analyses and chemical microanalysis in the determination of structural damage incurred in the historical time in relation to the effect of contemporary abiotic events;</jats:p>
<jats:p>• Application of a standard medical computer-assisted tomograph in qualitative assessment of structure and observations of mechanisms of failure in the cement/peat soil composite.</jats:p>
<jats:p>Investigations concerning the applicability of computed tomography in soil micromechanics are demonstrative in character and the presented conclusions suggest further directions for research.</jats:p>
title: Microstructural and Tomographic Analyses in Geotechnical Assessment of Soil Media
